The Prudential Insurance Company ofAmerica, a privately held company, said today that net incomein 1986 rose to 2.8 billion dlrs from the 2.3 billion dlrsreported the year earlier.    Assets under management rose to 177.5 billion dlrs in 1986from 150.1 billion dlrs in 1985, while consolidated assetsjumped to 134.5 billion dlrs from 115.7 billion dlrs.    Discussing its major subsidiaries, the company said thatPrudential Capital and Investment Services Inc, the holdingcompany for brokerage house Prudential-Bache Securities andcertain other related subsidiaries, earned 142 million dlrs in1986. Of that, the securities operations of Prudential-Bachenetted 81.7 mln dlrs after taxes and a charge of 25 mln dlrs. Reuter&#3;